INSERT INTO `mobs` VALUES (461,'/images/mobs/mobs_461.png','Safeguard of the Witchbane Ruins\' basement cellar. Mysteriously rare and highly unconventional.',NULL,'Witchbane Ruins','Arcane Sphere Of Faces','[\"None\"]',NULL),(462,'/images/mobs/mobs_462.png','The Giant Bats of Limgrave are nocturnal creatures and often rest during the day, unless they are disturbed.',NULL,'Near the cliffs on Western Limgrave.','Giant Bat','[\"Gold Firefly\"]',NULL),(463,'/images/mobs/mobs_463.png','Feral, often massive bears with runic patterns on their chest. Most commonly found scavenging the realms of The Lands Between or fighting other wild creatures.',NULL,'Eastern Limgrave, Weeping Peninsula','Lesser Runebear','[\"Hefty Beast Bone\", \"16 Runes\"]',NULL),(464,'/images/mobs/mobs_464.png','Bizarre catterpillar-shaped beings formed of moss-covered spherical stones and a disturbing eye that looks like that of a human being. They are commonly found as dull groups of seemingly lifeless rocks.',NULL,'Evergaol Structures','Abnormal Stone Cluster','[\"Ruin Fragments\", \"\", \"39 Runes\"]',NULL),(465,'/images/mobs/mobs_465.png','???',NULL,'Ainsel River, Lake of Rot','Basilisk','[\"611 Runes\"]',NULL),(466,'/images/mobs/mobs_466.png','The servants of Stormveil come in many shapes, including Eagles that have been enslaved and fitted with blades. Driving them to attack those who approach',NULL,'Stormveil Castle','Bladed Talon Eagle','[\"98 Runes\", \"Warhawk\'s Talon\", \"Flight Pinion\"]',NULL),(467,'/images/mobs/mobs_467.png','The Boars of Limgrave are less aggressive than normal, but should not be assumed to be passive',NULL,'in Forests of Limgrave and Stormhill','Boar','[\"Thin Animal Bones\", \"Lump of Flesh\"]',NULL),(468,'/images/mobs/mobs_468.png','Burning Slugs move slowly and are located in the open field.',NULL,'Liurnia of The Lakes','Burning Slug','[\"Smoldering Butterfly\"]',NULL),(469,'/images/mobs/mobs_469.png','Crabs thrive in the shallow ponds of Agheel Lake and the shores of Limgrave',NULL,'Roaming the beaches of Western Limgrave.','Crab','[\"Crab Eggs\", \"Strip of White Flesh\"]',NULL),(470,'/images/mobs/mobs_470.png','An Enemy made by Enemies',NULL,'Sealed Tunnel','Construct','[\"-\"]',NULL),(471,'/images/mobs/mobs_471.png','Deer roam freely in the plains on Limgrave, now that hunters have all but disappeared',NULL,'West Limgrave, South West Liurnia of The Lakes','Deer','[\"Thin Animal Bones\", \"Sliver of Meat\", \"Beast Liver\", \"6 Runes\"]',NULL),(472,'/images/mobs/mobs_472.png','Roaming through the fields of Limgrave, wild Dogs should not be assumed to be docile nor dull.',NULL,'in Dragon-Burnt Ruins','Dog','[\"Thin Animal Bones\", \"Lump of Flesh\", \"52 Runes\"]',NULL),(473,'/images/mobs/mobs_473.png','The Great Dragonflies of Limgrave buzz and harass all creatures in their vicinity',NULL,'Agheel Lake, Limgrave','Giant Dragonfly','[\"Great Dragonfly Head\", \"5 Runes\"]',NULL),(474,'/images/mobs/mobs_474.png','Found alone or in small packs, these bloodthirsty beasts stalk the Lands Between with predatory fervor.',NULL,'Caria Manor, Liurnia of the Lakes','Direwolf','[\"371 Runes\"]',NULL),(475,'/images/mobs/mobs_475.png','Majestic Eagles can be spotted among the cliffs, even during these times.',NULL,'Limgrave / Stormhill','Eagle','[\"Flight Pinion\", \"Slumbering Egg\"]',NULL),(476,'/images/mobs/mobs_476.png','Giant Crabs crowd the shores and shallows, attacking any who approach by swinging their powerful claws and spewing forth high-pressure water.',NULL,'in the watery areas of Agheel Lake and the beaches of Western Limgrave','Giant Crab','[\"318 Runes\", \"Crab Eggs\", \"Strip of White Flesh\"]',NULL),(477,'/images/mobs/mobs_477.png','Giant Land Octopuses are a dangerous foe for any daring to visit the beaches of Limgrave.',NULL,'Commonly found in watery areas','Giant Land Octopus','[\"Land Octopus Ovary\", \"Strip of White Flesh\", \"187~336 Runes\"]',NULL),(478,'/images/mobs/mobs_478.png','The Lands Between are rife with all manner of life forms, naturally evolving over long periods and adapting to the environment. One such creature is the Giant Lobster — a creature that evolved to grow to such enormous sizes in order to better defend itself against much deadlier threats.',NULL,'Liurnia of the Lakes','Giant Lobster','[\"Strip of White Flesh\", \"\", \"Crab Eggs\"]',NULL),(479,'/images/mobs/mobs_479.png','Giant Poison Flowers sprout in unlikely places, and summon down the elements on those who approach them',NULL,'within Post Town Remains in Limgrave.','Giant Poison Flower','[\"256 Runes\"]',NULL),(480,'/images/mobs/mobs_480.png','???',NULL,'Limgrave, Weeping Peninsula, Altus Plateau','Giant Rat','[\"Golden Rune [3]\", \"Giant Rat Ashes\"]',NULL),(481,'/images/mobs/mobs_481.png','The Guillemot on the beaches of Limgrave are docile animals, but they are easily spooked',NULL,'Roaming the beaches of Western Limgrave.','Guillemot','[\"Flight Pinion\", \"Four-Toed Fowl Foot\", \"6 Runes\"]',NULL),(482,'/images/mobs/mobs_482.png','Feral, often massive bears with runic patterns on their chest. Most commonly found scavenging the realms of The Lands Between or fighting other wild creatures.',NULL,'Eastern Limgrave, Weeping Peninsula','Lesser Runebear','[\"Hefty Beast Bone\", \"16 Runes\"]',NULL),(483,'/images/mobs/mobs_483.png','Hostile, over-sized wolves majestically covered in scarlet fur.',NULL,'Liurnia of The Lakes','Lesser Red Wolf Of Radagon','[\"4158 Runes\"]',NULL),(484,'/images/mobs/mobs_484.png','Lesser Spider Hands are horrific creatures, surpassed only by their more powerful, gigantic counterparts.',NULL,'Caria Manor, Liurnia of the Lakes, Mountaintops of the Giants','Lesser Spider Hand','[\"???\"]',NULL),(485,'/images/mobs/mobs_485.png','The peculiar Land Octopus is a rather small but dangerous creature',NULL,'In the watery areas of Agheel Lake and the beaches of Western Limgrave','Land Octopus','[\"12~13 Runes\", \"Sometimes: Land Octopus Ovary\"]',NULL),(486,'/images/mobs/mobs_486.png','Owls can be resting on the cliffs of Stormhill, and would even seem friendly and unconcerned by those passing by',NULL,'perched on cliffs around Limgrave and Stormhill','Owl','[\"Moon Egg\"]',NULL),(487,'/images/mobs/mobs_487.png','Poison Flowers grow near caves and cellars in Limgrave',NULL,'within Waypoint Ruins in Limgrave.','Poison Flower','[\"14 Runes\", \"Poisonbloom\"]',NULL),(488,'/images/mobs/mobs_488.png','Land Squirts are repulsive shallow water creatures that emit a poison mist to kill and devour those nearby',NULL,'Dragon-Burnt Ruins, Shores of Limgrave','Land Squirt','[\"13 Runes\"]',NULL),(489,'/images/mobs/mobs_489.png','Giant rats plague the mines and caves of Limgrave, spreading diseases where they go',NULL,'Limgrave Tunnels, Ailing Village, Tombsward Cave','Rat','[\"Pauper\'s Rune\", \"Rune Arc\", \"Golden Rune (1)\", \"13 Runes\"]',NULL),(490,'/images/mobs/mobs_490.png','A species unique to The Lands Between, as adorable as scared.',NULL,'Limgrave, South West Liurnia of the Lakes, ','Rabbitgaroo','[\"Thin Animal Bones\", \"Sliver of Meat\"]',NULL),(491,'/images/mobs/mobs_491.png','Undead dogs haunt the depths of Limgrave\'s mines, attacking all those who dwell into the tunnels',NULL,'Limgrave Tunnels','Rotten Stray','[\"Thin Beast Bones\", \"52~55 Runes\"]',NULL),(492,'/images/mobs/mobs_492.png','The sheep from Limgrave have long forgotten captivity, romaing the landscape freely instead.',NULL,'in the pastures of Limgrave and Stormhill','Sheep','[\"Thin Beast Bones\", \"Sliver of Meat\", \"Beast Liver\", \"6 Runes\"]',NULL),(493,'/images/mobs/mobs_493.png','Skeletal slime drudges the shores and shallows of Limgrave, looking for prey to consume',NULL,'in the watery areas of Agheel Lake and the beaches of Western Limgrave','Skeletal Slime','[\"Glass Shard\", \"16~18 Runes\"]',NULL),(494,'/images/mobs/mobs_494.png','Spirit Jellyfish are passive creatures seeking to protect, unless angered',NULL,'Cemetery, west of Stormhill','Spirit Jellyfish','[\"16 Runes\"]',NULL),(495,'/images/mobs/mobs_495.png','There are both Crimson and Cerulean Teardrop Scarabs. Defeat them to replenish the flasks that match their type.',NULL,NULL,'Teardrop Scarab',NULL,NULL),(496,'/images/mobs/mobs_496.png','Spider Hands skitter about their environs, often clinging to walls to put the drop on unsuspecting trespassers. They are also capable of burrowing deep beneath the earth, violently bursting out of the ground to grab and crush their prey.',NULL,'Caria Manor, Liurnia of the Lakes, Mountaintops of the Giants','Spider Hand','[\"Somber Smithing Stone (2), Somber Smithing Stone (7)\"]',NULL),(497,'/images/mobs/mobs_497.png','Wild Mouflons become hostile when threatened and fight their aggressors by charging forward and striking them with their large horns.',NULL,'Stormhill','Wild Mouflon','[\"None\"]',NULL),(498,'/images/mobs/mobs_498.png','Turtles are passive creatures almost driven to extinction by those seeking its meat, said to have curative properties',NULL,'West Limgrave','Turtle','[\"Turtle Neck Meat\", \"5 Runes\"]',NULL),(499,'/images/mobs/mobs_499.png','Wolves hunt the Lands Between in packs, and all those traveling should beware of their dangerous pack leaders',NULL,'Limgrave, Groveside Cave','Wolf','[\"Thin Animal Bones\", \"Lump of Flesh\", \"66 Runes\"]',NULL),(500,'/images/mobs/mobs_500.png','Hostile over-developed creatures resembling large shrimps. Remarkably agile.',NULL,'Sellia Crystal Tunnel, Caelid Waypoint Ruins','Prawn Miner','[\"612 Runes\"]',NULL),(501,'/images/mobs/mobs_501.png','Farum Azula Dragons fly around the Farum Azula or what\'s left of it, if any of them notice someone roaming around, they will come to hunt the down. They have the power of thunder and they will use it aggresively towards enemies.',NULL,'Crumbling Farum Azula','Farum Azula Dragon','[\"Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone\", \"\", \"32,400 Runes\"]',NULL),(502,'/images/mobs/mobs_502.png','Bloody Finger Nerijus follows the Bloody Finger code, hunting for fellow Tarnished without remorse',NULL,'Invades on the ravine leading north-east from Agheel Lake, toward Murkwater Catacombs','Bloody Finger Nerijus','[\"316 Runes\", \"Furcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Reduvia\"]',NULL),(503,'/images/mobs/mobs_503.png','Invaded by Anastasia, Tarnished-Eater!',NULL,'Smoldering Church, Limgrave','Anastasia, Tarnished-eater','[\"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Sacred Scorpion Charm\", \"\", \"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Butchering Knife\"]',NULL),(504,'/images/mobs/mobs_504.png',NULL,NULL,'Flame Peak, Mountaintops of the Giants','Bloody Finger Okina','[\"734 Runes\", \"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Rivers of Blood\", \"Okina Mask\"]',NULL),(505,'/images/mobs/mobs_505.png','Edgar the Revenger is a warrior clad in medium armor and wields a halberd. His moveset involves mostly physical attacks and his poise is easily broken with magic.',NULL,'Revenger\'s Shack, Liurnia of the Lakes','Edgar The Revenger','[\"316 Runes\", \"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Shabriri Grape\", \"Banished Knight\'s Halberd (+8)\", \"Raw Meat Dumpling x 5\"]',NULL),(506,'/images/mobs/mobs_506.png','???',NULL,'Volcano Manor','Inquisitor Ghiza','[\"316 Runes\", \"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Ghiza\'s Wheel\"]',NULL),(507,'/images/mobs/mobs_507.png','???',NULL,'Roundtable Hall','Mad Tongue Alberich','[\"Taunter\'s Tongue\"]',NULL),(508,'/images/mobs/mobs_508.png','Maleigh Marais\'s identity is completely shrouded by their mask and long robes. They are equipped with a rapier and move carefully around opponents. They are easily staggered with magic attacks such as Glintblade Phalanx.',NULL,'Fields west of The Shaded Castle','Maleigh Marais, Shaded Castle Castellan','[\"4,800 Runes\", \"Antspur Rapier\", \"Marais Mask\", \"Marais Robe\"]',NULL),(509,'/images/mobs/mobs_509.png','Moongrum the Carian Knight is the guardian of Raya Lucaria Academy\'s Grand Library, he is the last line of defense against intruders who are wanting to slay the head sorcerer of the institute. Just like you, a Tarnished, Moongrum is capable of wielding two different weapons, a shield, can use sorcery, and even use Flasks to recover health. A true warrior of Raya Lucaria.',NULL,'Raya Lucaria Academy','Moongrum Carian Knight','[\"3000 Runes\", \"Carian Knight\'s Shield\"]',NULL),(510,'/images/mobs/mobs_510.png','???',NULL,'Carian Study Hall','Preceptor Miriam','[\"Magic Downpour\", \"Lucidity\"]',NULL),(511,'/images/mobs/mobs_511.png','Invaded by Recusant Henricus!',NULL,'East of Stormhill Shack','Recusant Henricus','[\"Furlcalling Finger Remedy, Hammer Talisman\"]',NULL),(512,'/images/mobs/mobs_512.png','Due to their comically large and round heads, Albinaurics are perpetually hunched-over. They are often found in groups of five or more and they employ rudimentary combat tactics, often attacking recklessly with repeated swings and long combos that leave them open. At times, you may spot an Albinauric performing quick cartwheels on the battlefield, displaying agility despite their stature.',NULL,'Liurnia of the Lakes','Albinauric','[\"???\"]',NULL),(513,'/images/mobs/mobs_513.png','Guarding the rooftops of Ordina.',NULL,'Ordina Liturgical Town','Albinauric Wolfback Archer','[\"Albinauric Bloodclot \", \"St. Trina\'s Arrow \", \"Blue Silver Mail Armor\"]',NULL),(514,'/images/mobs/mobs_514.png','A tall knight who was banished and bound to serve the Grafted Lord, and to kill those trespassers of Stormveil Castle. They are normally seen wielding a large weapon such as a longsword with a shield or a polearm, and they are fully protected with a complete set of armor.',NULL,'Stormveil Castle','Banished Knight','[\"400 Runes\", \"Banished Knight\'s Greatsword\", \"Banished Knight Set\", \"Banished Knight\'s Shield\", \"Banished Knight\'s Halberd\"]',NULL),(515,'/images/mobs/mobs_515.png','The Beastmen of Farum Azula are ferocious half-man, half-beast warriors. They display remarkable agility and are proficient in a plethora of weaponry including various curved blades, greatswords, shields and spears. Many are also excellent marksmen with their unique curved throwing knives which they use with deadly precision.',NULL,'Crumbling Farum Azula','Azula Beastman','[\"Sanctuary Stone\"]',NULL),(516,'/images/mobs/mobs_516.png','Assassins of the Two Fingers sent forth to carry out their dirty work',NULL,'Ainsel River Main','Baleful Shadow','[\"8561 Runes\"]',NULL),(517,'/images/mobs/mobs_517.png','Mysterious hooded figures belonging to an order of monks that call upon the power of the Black Flame, as well as their astute martial prowess to fell foes and trespassers of their domains.',NULL,'Divine Tower of Caelid','Blackflame Monk','[\"1,764 Runes\", \"Blackflame Monk Armor\"]',NULL),(518,'/images/mobs/mobs_518.png','???',NULL,'Leyndell Royal Capital','Perfumer','[\"563 Runes\"]',NULL),(519,'/images/mobs/mobs_519.png','The Black Knight, riding atop a dark steed, wielding a mighty halberd.',NULL,'Limgrave, south-east of the telescope, patrolling on a bridge ','Black Knight','[\"935 Runes\"]',NULL),(520,'/images/mobs/mobs_520.png','Wielders of heavy swords and spears, protected by large shields and fully armored. These Knights are often aided in combat by soldiers or hostile dogs, therefore posing a threat to the unprepared and novice.',NULL,'Limgrave','Godrick Knight','[\"260 Runes\"]',NULL),(521,'/images/mobs/mobs_521.png','Castle Guards comprise the bulk of Stormveil\'s defenses, but are by no means the most dangerous of the many great ones within.',NULL,'Stormveil Castle','Castle Guard','[\"114 Runes\", \"Exile Set\", \"Torchpole\", \"Stormhawk Feather\", \"Soldier\'s Crossbow\"]',NULL),(522,'/images/mobs/mobs_522.png','The Chanting Winged Dames of Liurnia of The Lakes are equally hostile as they are suspicious.',NULL,'Ruin-Strewn Precipice, Liurnia of The Lakes, Fort Faroth','Chanting Winged Dame','[\"Golden Rune [5]\"]',NULL),(523,'/images/mobs/mobs_523.png','???',NULL,'Siofra River, Ainsel River','Clayman','[\"120 Runes\"]',NULL),(524,'/images/mobs/mobs_524.png','The Commoner is a servant that is bound to perform duties for their superiors within Stormveil Castle. They appear to be tall, slender, yet weak, who is still capable of fighting trespassers.',NULL,'Stormveil Castle','Commoner','[\"67 Runes\", \"Commoner\'s Garb\", \"Commoner\'s Shoes\"]',NULL),(525,'/images/mobs/mobs_525.png','Agile and hostile, Demi-Humans scavenge the land in groups commanded by a leader, a stronger and more menacing creature. They roam the field light-armored and wielding a wide range of melee weapons and wooden shields.',NULL,'Caves and beaches of Limgrave, such as Dissenter\'s Cave.','Demi-human','[\"42 Runes\", \"Rainbow Stone\", \"Rickety Shield\", \"Falchion\", \"String\", \"Glowstone\", \"\", \"Rainbow Stone\"]',NULL),(526,'/images/mobs/mobs_526.png','Fire Monks hierarchically gather in ceremonies, often at night, burning their way through Liurnia of The Lakes with torches and Mobile Flamethrowers. Fire Monk Abbots have the powerful ability of bursting flames from their hands and must be fought carefully.',NULL,'East Liurnia of The Lakes','Fire Monk','[\"Fire Monk Hood\", \"Fire Monk Armor\", \"Fire Monk Gauntlets\", \"Fire Monk Greaves\", \"Monk\'s Flamemace\", \"Smouldering Butterfly\", \"Fire Blossom\"]',NULL),(527,'/images/mobs/mobs_527.png','Frail and malnourished, Diggers wield a glintstone-imbued staff for mining which doubles as a weapon when push comes to shove.',NULL,'Altus Tunnel','Sorcerer Miner','[\"Runes\", \"Digger\'s Staff\"]',NULL),(528,'/images/mobs/mobs_528.png','Flame Guardians are slender humanoids dressed in simple white garbs and wearing a bronze mask, concealing their identity. They are equipped with long, flaming poles/staves and wield fire magic.',NULL,'Guardians\' Garrison','Flame Guardian','[\"2,415 Runes\"]',NULL),(529,'/images/mobs/mobs_529.png','Glintstone Sorcerers are decked in Raya Lucarian Robes and distinct Glintstone Crown masks that obscure their identity. These scholars have access to lower level spells such as Glintstone Pebble, among others.',NULL,'Raya Lucaria Academy','Glintstone Sorcerer','[\"???\"]',NULL),(530,'/images/mobs/mobs_530.png','Hungry Gnolls are usually found eating from dead bodies which makes them vulnerable to surprise or stealth attacks, but they are quick and unforgivingly lethal. They come in different classes, some of the wield a sword and use it very acrobatically, other use shields and some even are able to cast thunder.',NULL,'Crumbling Farum Azola','Gnoll','[\"Sanctuary Stone\"]',NULL),(531,'/images/mobs/mobs_531.png','The Godrick Soldiers of the Lands Between now roam the landscape, their clothes rags, hoping to rebuild their lives',NULL,'Gatefront Ruins, Castle Morne, Stormgate, Roaming the Limgrave landscape','Godrick Soldier','[\"64 - 77 Runes\"]',NULL),(532,'/images/mobs/mobs_532.png','Golems lay inactive in the hills of Stormhill, but those foolish enough to wake them will soon curse their fate',NULL,'West ruins of Stormhill., Castle Morne Entrance, Ainsel River Well, Leyndell, Royal Capital','Golem','[\"3x Smithing Stone Shard\", \"844~1039 Runes\"]',NULL),(533,'/images/mobs/mobs_533.png','Former foot soldiers who have turned to banditry. Clandestine and secluded from civilazation, now they lie in hidden caves.',NULL,'Murkwater Cave','Highwayman','[\"Bolt\", \"Smoldering Butterfly\", \"Highwayman Hood\"]',NULL),(534,'/images/mobs/mobs_534.png','Invading another world. Defeat Great Horned Tragoth!',NULL,'Ruin-Strewn Precipice','Great Horned Tragoth','[\"158 Runes\", \"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Rune Arc\", \"Bull-Goat Helm\", \"Bull-Goat Armor\", \"Bull-Goat Gauntlets\", \"Bull-Goat Greaves\"]',NULL),(535,'/images/mobs/mobs_535.png','Exceedingly tough and skillful Knight, a golden armor-wearing menace lethal to most. Highly trained warrior and a threatening adversary due to its fine combat skills.',NULL,'Liurnia of The Lakes','Gold Dragon Cult Knight','[\"Dragon Cult Prayerbook\", \"\", \"Leyndell Knight Set\", \"\"]',NULL),(536,'/images/mobs/mobs_536.png','Imps infest many catacombs in the Lands Between, although some theorize they could be protecting their secrets',NULL,'Within dungeons and catacombs','Imp','[\"Forked Hatchet\", \"40~67 Runes\"]',NULL),(537,'/images/mobs/mobs_537.png','Small and agile creatures that typically conceal themselves within a smokescreen., Often wielding an axe or a flail amd performing flying attacks.',NULL,'Ruin-Strewn Precipice','Imp Miner','[\"None\"]',NULL),(538,'/images/mobs/mobs_538.png','Sneak warriors, patient and quick to get in your back.',NULL,'Ordina Liturgical Town','Invisible Warrior','[\"Ghost Glovewort (9)\"]',NULL),(539,'/images/mobs/mobs_539.png','???',NULL,'Mountaintops of the Giants','Juno Hoslow, Knight Of Blood','[\"158 Runes\", \"Rune Arc\", \"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Hoslow\'s Petal Whip\", \"Hoslow\'s Helm\", \"Hoslow\'s Armor\", \"Hoslow\'s Gauntlets\", \"Hoslow\'s Greaves\"]',NULL),(540,'/images/mobs/mobs_540.png','Imps infest many catacombs in the Lands Between, although some theorize they could be protecting their secrets',NULL,'Within dungeons and catacombs','Imp','[\"Forked Hatchet\", \"40~67 Runes\"]',NULL),(541,'/images/mobs/mobs_541.png','A living construct fashioned after felines and hounds, made to watch over catacombs. These constructs wield massive stone weaponry and are attuned to different elements.',NULL,'Giant-Conquering Hero\'s Grave','Lesser Burial Watchdog','[\"3,712 Runes\"]',NULL),(542,'/images/mobs/mobs_542.png','Knights of Zamor are slender humanoids with long hair, wielding a peculiar curved blade. These warriors are graceful and perform almost dance-like maneuvers as they weave across the battlefield. As denizens of the Mountaintops of the Giants, Knights of Zamor are strongly attuned to Frost, utilizing its powers to bolster their swordplay.',NULL,'Zamor Ruins','Knight Of Zamor','[\"5,039 Runes\"]',NULL),(543,'/images/mobs/mobs_543.png','The Lesser Pumpkin Head is a weaker variant of the Pumpkin Head. It appears to be an outcast due to its appearance and is mainly used as one of a weapon to fight against intruders and trespassers alike. The Lesser Pumpkin Head can be seen wearing a Pumpkin Helm, a distressed cloak, and wields a large club.',NULL,'Castle Morne, Raya Lucaria Academy, Limgrave','Lesser Pumpkin Head','[\"Pumpkin Helm\", \"Sanctuary Stone\", \"273~293 Runes\"]',NULL),(544,'/images/mobs/mobs_544.png','A guardian that sleeps deep within the crypt of Stormveil Castle. It is quick and very aggressive when it attacks and moves similar to a centipede with its multiple legs. The Lesser Ulcerated Tree Spirit also features two large arms and a tail that it mainly uses to swing around or to slam the ground.',NULL,'Stormveil Castle','Lesser Ulcerated Tree Spirit','[\"Runes\", \"Golden Seed\"]',NULL),(545,'/images/mobs/mobs_545.png','The Living Jar, a walking vase that has long arms used for reaching and attacking their foes. A Living Jar may appear small in a group and it can also appear as a singular giant entity, capable of using slow, yet strong attacks.',NULL,'Multiple Locations','Living Jar','[\"Living Jar Shard\"]',NULL),(546,'/images/mobs/mobs_546.png','Lesser Wormface may not be as large as Wormface itself but they can be found roaming around in groups around Crumbling Farum Azula.',NULL,'Crumbling Farum Azula','Lesser Wormface','[\"Gold-Tinged Excrement\"]',NULL),(547,'/images/mobs/mobs_547.png','Large wagons operated from the inside that shoot fire from a sculpture\'s mouth.',NULL,'Liurnia of The Lakes','Maneuverable Flamethrower','[\"None\"]',NULL),(548,'/images/mobs/mobs_548.png','The Marionette Gargoyle are statues within Raya Lucaria Academy that have been reanimated with magical properties. They mainly fly in the air and wield a scythe that they use to attack their foes. They are usually found on posts, pretending to be statues.',NULL,'Raya Lucaria Academy','Marionette Gargoyle','[\"Runes\"]',NULL),(549,'/images/mobs/mobs_549.png','Marionette Soldiers are puppets that are created and given life by superior being that reside within Raya Lucaria Academy. Their purpose is to protect and stop intruders from entering the institute. These soldiers appear to have multiple arms wielding more than one weapon, making them unpredictable in regards to how they will strike.',NULL,'Raya Lucaria Academy, Academy Gate Town, Raya Lucaria Crystal Tunnel, Witchbane Ruins','Marionette Soldier','[\"Marionette Soldier Helm\"]',NULL),(550,'/images/mobs/mobs_550.png','The ever working miners of Limgrave know no life but their toil, and will fiercely defend it',NULL,'Limgrave Tunnels, Sellia Crystal Tunnel, Ruin-Strewn Precipice','Miner','[\"92 Runes\", \"Explosive Stone\", \"Smithing Stone [1]\"]',NULL),(551,'/images/mobs/mobs_551.png','Mounted Northern Mercenaries are often seen guarding important deliveries and outposts, such as Stormgate',NULL,'Limgrave','Mounted Northern Mercenary','[\"282 Runes\", \"Dismounter\", \"Kaiden Helm\", \"Kaiden Armor\", \"Kaiden Gauntlets\", \"Kaiden Trousers\"]',NULL),(552,'/images/mobs/mobs_552.png',NULL,NULL,'North-east region of Limgrave, North of Liurnia of the Lakes','Mounted Knight','[\"Ash of War: Golden Vow\"]',NULL),(553,'/images/mobs/mobs_553.png','Noble Sorcerers are frail old men wearing tattered garbs and a dirty yellow cape. They use a standard glintstone staff as both a sorcery catalyst and walking stick.',NULL,'Various','Noble Sorcerer','[\"Glintstone Staff\"]',NULL),(554,'/images/mobs/mobs_554.png','The Misbegotten are small humanoid creatures with small wings on their backs and a tail that reaches to the ground. Treated as slaves or worse from the time they are born, they rush in attack wildly and ruthlessly with their Iron Cleavers.',NULL,'Castle Morne, Weeping Peninsula, Mt. Gelmir','Misbegotten','[\"Iron Cleaver\", \"Old Fang\", \"59 Runes\"]',NULL),(555,'/images/mobs/mobs_555.png','Kaiden Sellswords roam the land, looking to be hired for several protection roles',NULL,'Throughout Limgrave and Stormhill','Kaiden Sellsword','[\"282 Runes \", \"Dismounter\", \"\", \"Frozen Raisin\", \"Kaiden Helm\", \"Kaiden Armor\", \"Kaiden Gauntlets\", \"Kaiden Trousers\"]',NULL),(556,'/images/mobs/mobs_556.png','A large ogre that is kept imprisoned within the grounds of Stormveil Castle. It appears to be battered and treated violently to discipline it, and used as a weapon to fight against trespassers.',NULL,'Stormveil Castle','Omen','[\"Runes\", \"Omen Cleaver\"]',NULL),(557,'/images/mobs/mobs_557.png','A golden statue that sits on a small wagon. Attached to it are two pendulum blades that can extend to capture its prey. The Pendulum Statue is being controlled by an unkown creature that rests within it, only by opening its chest will it reveal its root-like tentacles.',NULL,'Raya Lucaria Academy','Pendulum Statue','[\"Runes\"]',NULL),(558,'/images/mobs/mobs_558.png','Invading another world. Defeat Old Knight Istvan!',NULL,'Stormhill','Old Knight Istvan','[\"84 Runes\", \"Rune Arc\", \"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Scaled Helm\", \"Scaled Armor\", \"Scaled Gauntlets\", \"Scaled Greaves\"]',NULL),(559,'/images/mobs/mobs_559.png','???',NULL,'Leyndell Royal Capital','Perfumer','[\"563 Runes\"]',NULL),(560,'/images/mobs/mobs_560.png','The breaking disrupted the flora and fauna of the region. Some took a rather intense liking to the larger plants that emerged',NULL,'Castle Morne, Weeping Peninsula','Pumpkin Head','[\"291 Runes\", \"Pumpkin Helm\", \"Sanctuary Stone\"]',NULL),(561,'/images/mobs/mobs_561.png','Academicians of the Raya Lucaria Academy. These sholars dedicate their lives to learning and mastering the art of sorcery and serve one superiror sorcerer who resides within the institute. They are able to use glintstone sorcery to strike their foes from afar, and are still capable of using their weapon for close-quarters combat.',NULL,'Raya Lucaria Academy','Raya Lucaria Sorcerer','[\"Academy Glintstone Staff\", \"Raya Lucarian Robe\", \"Sorcerer Manchettes\", \"Sorcerer Leggings\"]',NULL),(562,'/images/mobs/mobs_562.png','Invading another world. Defeat Rileigh the Idle!',NULL,'Altus Plateau','Rileigh The Idle','[\"84 Runes\", \"Rune Arc\", \"Furlcalling Finger Remedy\", \"Crepus\'s Vial\", \"Black-Key Bolt x20\"]',NULL),(563,'/images/mobs/mobs_563.png','A grotesque amalgamation of limbs, the Revenant is a creature with the body structure of an arachnid and the face of a human. Much like a spider, it possesses many limbs that seem to have been grafted onto its body, taken from diseased humans. The Revenant is capable of traveling through portals it creates with a peculiar form of magic, swiftly emerging behind a foe to catch them off guard.',NULL,'Liurnia of the Lakes','Revenant','[\"4,103 Runes\", \"Ghost Glovewort (2)\", \"Rowa Fruit\"]',NULL),(564,'/images/mobs/mobs_564.png','Servants of Rot relish in the pungent miasma expelled by Poison Flowers. Their bodies are heavily mutated by the rot, their heads transformed into large crowns of fungi. These presumably former humans know only the rot and they worship it like a deity, bathed in its fog of decay.',NULL,'Stillwater Cave, Caelid Waypoint Ruins','Servant Of Rot','[\"Toxic Mushroom\"]',NULL),(565,'/images/mobs/mobs_565.png','Wardens roam the halls of the Raya Lucaria Academy, armed and watchful for furtive marauders.',NULL,'Raya Lucaria Academy','Raya Lucarian Warden','[\"None\"]',NULL),(566,'/images/mobs/mobs_566.png','Soldiers defend the many outposts of the Lords from incoming threats, such as the Tarnished',NULL,'Stormveil Castle, Stormhill, Main Limgrave, Weeping Peninsula','Soldier','[\"33~64 Runes\", \"Lordsworn\'s Straight Sword\", \"Dagger\"]',NULL),(567,'/images/mobs/mobs_567.png','Skeleton Mages are usually found on graveyards in Liurnia of the Lakes. They can out from the ground, they can be found in groups, wielding scythes and constantly casting a spell launching ghostly skulls against you.',NULL,'Liurnia of the Lakes','Skeleton Mage','[\"108 Runes\"]',NULL),(568,'/images/mobs/mobs_568.png','Skeletons rise from cemeteries and ruins of the Lands Between, attacking relentlessly any who approach',NULL,'In the beaches and dungeons of Limgrave, and in the cemetery area of Stormhill','Skeleton','[\"35 Runes\"]',NULL),(569,'/images/mobs/mobs_569.png','A rare and long-haired creature, tall and slender, often found at the shore.',NULL,'Seaside Ruins','Slender Wayfarer','[\"311 Runes\", \"Ash of War: Gravitas\"]',NULL),(570,'/images/mobs/mobs_570.png','Nimble warriors protecting and patrolling the eternal cities.',NULL,'Night\'s Sacred Ground','Swordstress','[\"635 Runes\", \"Nox Swordstress Armor\"]',NULL),(571,'/images/mobs/mobs_571.png','The Trolls of the Lands Between are frequently enslaved for defensive positions, but are also used in lieu of beasts of burden',NULL,'Along the road north of the Collapsed bridge','Troll','[\"≈1000 Runes\", \"Smithing Stone Shard\"]',NULL),(572,'/images/mobs/mobs_572.png','Trolls are often employed to guard key locations, such as staircases large enough to accommodate their massive bodies. Often unmatched in strength, it bears the question... What manner of creature poses enough of a threat such that the mighty troll would find itself in need of heavy armor...?',NULL,'Caria Manor, Liurnia of the Lakes','Troll Knight','[\"???\"]',NULL),(573,'/images/mobs/mobs_573.png','Undead creatures, decayed and struggling to maintain balance while roaming the fields of The Lands Between.',NULL,'Fringefolk Hero\'s Grave, Dragon-Burnt Ruins','Undead Soldier','[\"19 Runes\"]',NULL),(574,'/images/mobs/mobs_574.png','Twinsage Sorcerers are distinguished from other scholars by the crowns worn on their head, depicting the Twinsage Conspectus, with distinct blue crystals forming at the top of the twin heads.',NULL,'Raya Lucaria Academy','Twinsage Sorcerer','[\"???\"]',NULL),(575,'/images/mobs/mobs_575.png','As their name suggests, Wraith Callers are equipped with Wraith Calling Bells that they use to channel death magic, summoning vengeful spirits to attack those that dare intrude upon the ruins of Liurnia. Devout worshippers of the Revenants, Wraith Callers are able to utilize the Revenants\' dimensional portals, albeit to a lesser extent.',NULL,'Liurnia of the Lakes','Wraith Caller','[\"Grave Violet\"]',NULL);
